  grammar:[
    {t:"La voz pasiva (passive voice)",form:"ser + past participle (+ por + agent)",ex:["El libro fue escrito por García Márquez. | The book was written by García Márquez.","La casa fue construida en 1990. | The house was built in 1990.","Los precios fueron aumentados. | The prices were raised.","El contrato fue firmado. | The contract was signed.","¿Por quién fue pintado? | By whom was it painted?"]},
    {t:"Se pasiva / se impersonal",form:"se + verb (3rd person)",ex:["Se habla español aquí. | Spanish is spoken here.","Se venden apartamentos. | Apartments for sale.","Se dice que es bueno. | They say it's good.","Se necesita experiencia. | Experience is needed.","¿Cómo se dice en español? | How do you say it in Spanish?"]},
    {t:"Estilo indirecto (reported speech)",form:"dijo que + imperfecto / condicional",ex:["Dijo que estaba cansada. | She said she was tired.","Me dijo que vendría. | He told me he would come.","Preguntó dónde vivía yo. | She asked where I lived.","Dijo que había terminado. | He said he had finished.","Afirmó que era verdad. | She claimed it was true."]},
    {t:"Cláusulas de relativo",form:"que (people/things), quien (people), donde (places), cuyo/a (whose)",ex:["El hombre que llamó es mi jefe. | The man who called is my boss.","La ciudad donde nací. | The city where I was born.","La chica a quien vi. | The girl whom I saw.","El libro cuyo autor es famoso. | The book whose author is famous.","El día en que nos conocimos. | The day on which we met."]}
  ],
  vocab:[
    {w:"a pesar de",es:"despite / in spite of",syn:"aunque, sin embargo",ex:["A pesar de la lluvia, salimos. | Despite the rain, we went out.","A pesar de todo, sigo adelante. | In spite of everything, I carry on.","A pesar de ser difícil, lo logré. | Despite being hard, I managed it.","A pesar del frío, corrí. | Despite the cold, I ran.","A pesar de sus errores, ganó. | Despite his mistakes, he won."]},
    {w:"vale la pena",es:"it's worth it",syn:"merece la pena",ex:["Vale la pena intentarlo. | It's worth trying.","¿Vale la pena ir? | Is it worth going?","No vale la pena preocuparse. | It's not worth worrying.","Siempre vale la pena aprender. | It's always worth learning.","La espera valió la pena. | The wait was worth it."]},
    {w:"destacar",es:"to stand out",syn:"sobresalir, brillar",ex:["Ella destaca en el trabajo. | She stands out at work.","¿Qué te hace destacar? | What makes you stand out?","Destacó entre los candidatos. | He stood out among the candidates.","Su trabajo destaca por su calidad. | Her work stands out for its quality.","Quiero destacar en español. | I want to excel in Spanish."]},
    {w:"no obstante",es:"nevertheless / however",syn:"sin embargo, aunque así",ex:["Es caro; no obstante, lo compramos. | It's expensive; nevertheless, we bought it.","No obstante, seguimos adelante. | Nevertheless, we carried on.","No obstante sus problemas, sonreía. | Despite his problems, he smiled.","No obstante, el plan funcionó. | Nevertheless, the plan worked.","No obstante las dificultades... | Despite the difficulties..."]}
  ],
  idioms:[["Estar en el ajo","To be in the know","Ella siempre está en el ajo. | She's always in the know."],["Poner los puntos sobre las íes","To set the record straight","Voy a poner los puntos sobre las íes. | I'm going to set the record straight."],["No hay mal que por bien no venga","Every cloud has a silver lining","Perdí el vuelo, pero conocí a mi pareja. ¡No hay mal que por bien no venga! | I missed the flight but met my partner. Every cloud has a silver lining!"],["A buenas horas","About time / too little too late","A buenas horas llega. | He arrives about time."],["Salir el tiro por la culata","To backfire","El plan le salió por la culata. | The plan backfired on him."]],
  reading:{text:["Mudarse a una ciudad nueva puede ser un punto de inflexión en tu vida, aunque rara vez es fácil. Cuando llegué, no conocía a nadie y me costaba orientarme. A pesar de las dificultades, lo que más me ayudó fue obligarme a hablar con desconocidos. No obstante, al principio era muy incómodo. Mirando atrás, esos momentos incómodos eran exactamente lo que necesitaba para crecer."],tr:"Moving to a new city can be a turning point in your life, although it's rarely easy. When I arrived, I didn't know anyone and struggled to get around. Despite the difficulties, what helped me most was forcing myself to talk to strangers. Nevertheless, at first it was very uncomfortable. Looking back, those uncomfortable moments were exactly what I needed to grow.",q:["¿Qué puede ser mudarse? | What can moving be?","¿Cómo se sentía al principio? | How did she feel at first?","¿Qué le ayudó más? | What helped her the most?","¿Cómo era al principio hablar con desconocidos? | How was it to talk to strangers?","¿Qué representaron esos momentos incómodos? | What were those uncomfortable moments?"]},
  listening:[["Extra en Español (Netflix-style)","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=extra+en+espanol+episodios"],["SpanishPod101 B2","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=spanishpod101+b2+intermediate+advanced"],["Spanish movies with subtitles","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=spanish+movie+clip+subtitles"],["Noticias en español lento","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=noticias+en+espanol+lento+aprender"],["News in Slow Spanish","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=news+in+slow+spanish+podcast"]],
  writing:["Argue for or against remote work in Spanish.","Describe a turning point in your life.","Write a movie review using relative clauses.","Rewrite a dialogue in reported speech (estilo indirecto).","Write a hypothetical situation using si + subjuntivo + condicional."],
  speaking:["Debate with yourself: 2 points for and 2 against a topic.","Tell an anecdote using pretérito + imperfecto together.","Shadowing: mimic 30 seconds of a Spanish speaker.","Describe what you would do if you won the lottery.","Give your opinion and qualify it (no obstante, a pesar de)."],
