B1:{
  cando:"I can discuss past experiences, give opinions, and start using the subjunctive in French.",
  tenses:[
    {n:"Imparfait (imperfect)",form:"-ais/-ais/-ait/-ions/-iez/-aient (stem from nous présent)",use:"Background, habits, ongoing states in the past.",ex:["Quand j'étais enfant, je jouais au foot. | When I was a child, I played football.","Elle étudiait tous les jours. | She used to study every day.","Il pleuvait quand je suis arrivé/e. | It was raining when I arrived.","Nous habitions à Chicago. | We were living in Chicago.","Qu'est-ce que tu faisais le dimanche? | What did you use to do on Sundays?"]},
    {n:"Futur simple",form:"-infinitive + ai/-as/-a/-ons/-ez/-ont",use:"Future plans and predictions.",ex:["Demain je parlerai à mon chef. | Tomorrow I'll talk to my boss.","Elle voyagera en France. | She will travel to France.","Quand reviendras-tu? | When will you return?","Nous étudierons ensemble. | We will study together.","Il y aura beaucoup de monde. | There will be many people."]},
    {n:"Subjonctif: introduction",form:"que + subj: endings -e/-es/-e/-ions/-iez/-ent",use:"After verbs of wanting, emotion, doubt; after 'il faut que'.",ex:["Je veux que tu viennes. | I want you to come.","Il faut que tu étudies. | You need to study.","J'espère qu'il fait beau. | I hope the weather is nice. (indicatif after espérer)","Je doute qu'il soit là. | I doubt he's there.","C'est important que vous parliez. | It's important that you speak."]}
  ],
  grammar:[
    {t:"Y & en (object pronouns)",form:"y = there/to it · en = some/of it",ex:["Tu vas en France? — J'y vais demain. | Are you going to France? — I'm going there tomorrow.","Tu veux du café? — J'en veux bien. | Do you want coffee? — I'd like some.","Il y a beaucoup de monde. | There are many people.","J'en ai besoin. | I need some (of it).","On y va? | Shall we go (there)?"]},
    {t:"Pronoms COD & COI",form:"COD: me/te/le/la/nous/vous/les · COI: me/te/lui/nous/vous/leur",ex:["Je le vois chaque jour. | I see him every day.","Je l'ai acheté hier. | I bought it yesterday.","Je lui ai donné le livre. | I gave him/her the book.","Tu peux m'aider? | Can you help me?","Je te rappelle plus tard. | I'll call you back later."]},
    {t:"Connecteurs logiques",form:"pourtant, cependant, donc, puisque, bien que",ex:["Il pleuvait; pourtant nous sommes sortis. | It was raining; yet we went out.","C'était difficile; cependant j'ai réussi. | It was hard; however I succeeded.","Je suis resté/e parce que j'étais malade. | I stayed because I was sick.","Il était tard, donc je suis parti/e. | It was late, so I left.","Bien qu'il soit tard, je continue. | Although it's late, I continue."]}
  ],
  vocab:[
    {w:"améliorer",es:"to improve",syn:"progresser, avancer",ex:["Je veux améliorer mon français. | I want to improve my French.","Elle a beaucoup amélioré. | She improved a lot.","La pratique améliore tout. | Practice improves everything.","Comment puis-je m'améliorer? | How can I improve?","Ta prononciation s'est améliorée. | Your pronunciation has improved."]},
    {w:"en fait",es:"actually / in fact",syn:"en réalité, vraiment",ex:["En fait, je ne sais pas. | Actually, I don't know.","C'est en fait plus facile. | It's actually easier.","En fait, tu as raison. | Actually, you're right.","Je ne l'ai pas fait, en fait. | I actually didn't do it.","En fait, c'est vrai. | Actually, that's true."]},
    {w:"cependant",es:"however / nevertheless",syn:"pourtant, néanmoins",ex:["C'est difficile; cependant j'essaie. | It's hard; however I try.","Cependant, les prix ont augmenté. | However, prices went up.","Je suis d'accord. Cependant... | I agree. However...","Cependant, on continue. | Nevertheless, we carry on.","C'est cher; cependant ça vaut la peine. | It's expensive; however it's worth it."]},
    {w:"avoir envie de",es:"to feel like / to want to",syn:"vouloir, désirer",ex:["J'ai très envie de te voir. | I really want to see you.","J'ai envie de manger une pizza. | I feel like eating pizza.","Tu as envie de sortir? | Do you feel like going out?","Je n'ai pas envie d'étudier. | I don't feel like studying.","Elle a envie de voyager. | She feels like traveling."]}
  ],
  idioms:[["Mettre les pieds dans le plat","To put your foot in it","J'ai mis les pieds dans le plat. | I put my foot in it."],["Avoir le cafard","To feel down / blue","J'ai le cafard aujourd'hui. | I'm feeling blue today."],["Poser un lapin","To stand someone up","Il m'a posé un lapin. | He stood me up."],["Ça coûte les yeux de la tête","It costs an arm and a leg","Ce restaurant coûte les yeux de la tête. | That restaurant costs a fortune."],["Prendre son courage à deux mains","To pluck up courage","J'ai pris mon courage à deux mains. | I plucked up courage."]],
  dialog:[
    {t:"✈️ At the airport",lines:[["Agent","Bonjour. Votre passeport, s'il vous plaît.","Good morning. Your passport, please."],["You","Voilà.","Here it is."],["Agent","Vous avez des bagages à enregistrer?","Are you checking any bags?"],["You","Une valise seulement.","Just one suitcase."],["Agent","Très bien. Votre porte est la B12. Bon vol!","Very good. Your gate is B12. Have a nice flight!"]]}
  ],
  reading:{text:["Ça fait environ un an que j'apprends le français. Au début, tout me semblait très difficile et j'ai failli abandonner. Cependant, j'ai continué à pratiquer et maintenant je peux tenir des conversations basiques. La clé était de ne pas avoir peur de faire des erreurs. Si tu veux apprendre une nouvelle langue, il faut être patient avec toi-même et continuer, même quand c'est dur."],tr:"I've been learning French for about a year. At first, everything seemed very difficult and I almost gave up. However, I kept practicing and now I can hold basic conversations. The key was not being afraid of making mistakes. If you want to learn a new language, you need to be patient with yourself and keep going, even when it's hard.",q:["Depuis combien de temps apprend le français? | How long has he been learning French?","Comment ça lui semblait au début? | How did it seem at first?","Pourquoi a-t-il failli abandonner? | Why did he almost give up?","Qu'est-ce qu'il peut faire maintenant? | What can he do now?","Quelle était la clé? | What was the key?"]},
