C1:{
  cando:"I can use French with near-native fluency, catch cultural references, and write in formal or literary registers.",
  tenses:[
    {n:"Subjonctif passé",form:"avoir/être (subjonctif présent) + past participle",use:"Past actions in subjunctive contexts.",ex:["Je suis content qu'il soit venu. | I'm glad he came.","Bien qu'elle soit arrivée en retard. | Although she arrived late.","Il faut qu'ils aient fini avant lundi. | They need to have finished before Monday.","Je doute qu'il l'ait dit. | I doubt he said it.","C'est dommage que tu n'aies pas pu venir. | It's a shame you couldn't come."]},
    {n:"Conditionnel passé",form:"avoir/être (conditionnel) + past participle",use:"What would have happened.",ex:["J'aurais appelé, mais je n'avais pas ton numéro. | I would have called, but I didn't have your number.","Elle serait venue si elle avait pu. | She would have come if she could have.","Qu'est-ce que tu aurais fait? | What would you have done?","On serait arrivés plus tôt. | We would have arrived sooner.","Je n'aurais pas cru ça. | I wouldn't have believed that."]}
  ],
  grammar:[
    {t:"Phrases conditionnelles (all types)",form:"T1: si+présent+futur · T2: si+imparfait+conditionnel · T3: si+plus-que-parfait+conditionnel passé",ex:["Si tu étudies, tu réussiras. (T1) | If you study, you'll succeed.","Si j'avais de l'argent, je voyagerais. (T2) | If I had money, I would travel.","Si j'avais étudié, j'aurais réussi. (T3) | If I had studied, I would have succeeded.","Si j'étais plus jeune, je courrais plus. | If I were younger, I would run more.","Si seulement j'avais su... | If only I had known..."]},
    {t:"Connecteurs formels",form:"néanmoins, par conséquent, en outre, étant donné que, quoique",ex:["Étant donné qu'il n'y a pas de preuve, on écarte. | Given that there's no proof, we discard.","Par conséquent, nous concluons que... | Consequently, we conclude that...","En outre, les coûts ont augmenté. | Furthermore, costs have risen.","Néanmoins, le plan a fonctionné. | Nevertheless, the plan worked.","Quoiqu'il soit tard, je continue. | Although it's late, I continue."]},
    {t:"Nominalisation (formal register)",form:"verb/adj → noun",ex:["l'arrivée de = the arrival of","l'augmentation des prix = the rise in prices","la mise en œuvre du plan = the implementation of the plan","la réduction des coûts = the cost reduction","l'échec du projet = the failure of the project"]}
  ],
  vocab:[
    {w:"saper",es:"to undermine",syn:"affaiblir, éroder",ex:["Cela sape la confiance. | This undermines trust.","Le scandale a sapé sa réputation. | The scandal undermined his reputation.","La corruption sape les institutions. | Corruption undermines institutions.","Ne la dénigre pas; tu la sapes. | Don't belittle her; you're undermining her.","Cela sape le plan. | That undermines the plan."]},
    {w:"nuancé/e",es:"nuanced",syn:"subtil, avec des nuances",ex:["Une opinion nuancée. | A nuanced opinion.","Son argument est très nuancé. | His argument is very nuanced.","Une approche plus nuancée. | A more nuanced approach.","La réalité est plus nuancée. | Reality is more nuanced.","Un débat nuancé. | A nuanced debate."]},
    {w:"défendre / plaider pour",es:"to advocate for",syn:"soutenir, promouvoir",ex:["Je plaide pour l'éducation gratuite. | I advocate for free education.","Elle défend les droits humains. | She advocates for human rights.","L'avocat a plaidé pour son client. | The lawyer advocated for his client.","Défendre le changement est nécessaire. | Advocating for change is necessary.","Pour quoi plaides-tu? | What do you advocate for?"]}
  ],
  idioms:[["Tourner autour du pot","To beat around the bush","Arrête de tourner autour du pot! | Stop beating around the bush!"],["Jeter l'éponge","To throw in the towel","Il a jeté l'éponge. | He threw in the towel."],["À tout seigneur tout honneur","Give credit where it's due","À tout seigneur tout honneur. | Give credit where it's due."],["Mettre les points sur les i","To dot the i's / set the record straight","Je vais mettre les points sur les i. | I'll set the record straight."]],
  reading:{text:["L'idée que le talent seul détermine le succès est, au mieux, une demi-vérité. Si la capacité naturelle fournit indéniablement une longueur d'avance, c'est la capacité à persévérer face à l'échec qui, en termes généraux, distingue les grands réalisateurs. La recherche suggère que la persévérance — mélange de passion et d'effort soutenu — l'emporte souvent sur l'intelligence brute. Sans discipline, même les plus doués ont tendance à plafonner."],tr:"The idea that talent alone determines success is, at best, a half-truth. While natural ability undoubtedly provides a head start, it's the capacity to persevere through failure that, broadly speaking, sets high achievers apart. Research suggests that grit — a blend of passion and sustained effort — often outweighs raw intelligence. Without discipline, even the most gifted tend to plateau.",q:["Qu'est-ce qui est qualifié de 'demi-vérité'? | What is called a 'half-truth'?","Que fournit la capacité naturelle? | What does natural ability provide?","Qu'est-ce qui distingue les grands réalisateurs? | What distinguishes high achievers?","Que combine la 'persévérance'? | What does 'grit' combine?","Que se passe-t-il pour les doués sans discipline? | What happens to the gifted without discipline?"]},
